Scientists have found traces of compounds in camomile and yarrow in the plaque of 50,000 year old Neanderthal teeth found in El Sidron, Spain . 
  They say Neanderthals may have used herbs to flavour their meat . 
  It is already known that they cooked their food and may have cooked grains of barley . 
  But new research suggests they could have used them to flavour food . 
  Researchers at the National Museum of Natural History in Paris say they may have been the first gourmet chefs . 
 